credit.credit-words: Publish, spread to all around the great Jehovah's name, Let the trumpet's martial sound the Lord of hosts proclaim: Praise Him in the sacred dance, harmony's full concert raise, Let the virgin choir advance, and move but to His praise.

Him, in whom they move and live, let every creature sing, Glory to their maker give, and homage to their King. Hallowed be Thy name beneath, as in Heaven on earth adored; Praise the Lord in every breath, let all things praise the Lord.
Praise the Lord who reigns above
